labels: [['The hotel has beach access.'], ['The hote is on the beach. They have a ping pong room. The staff can all dance and sing. They also had hula hoop and limbo contests, and hermit crab races. They had Casino Night where customers can do gambling with play money and dancing. They had a Campfire sing-along, Karaoke night and the Farewell show where they showed a video montage of pictures from the week. Other daytime activities included tennis, yoga, golf, wine country tours, softball game with staff vs. the vacationers. Customers can hire a babysitter.'], ["They have a copy of Alice's Adventure in Wonderland as a substitute."], [''], [''], [''], [''], [''], [''], ['The hotel offers Hiking, Golf. The room offers views of Tucson at night.'], [''], ['The hotel has a river with boat tours in their looby. They do a Christmas presentation as well.'], ['The hotel is a casino. labels: [[''], [''], ['The hotel gives access to a waterslide, free use of the driving range and putting greens with a bag of clubs, mountain bikes and helmets. preds: ['The hotel has a club. If you looking for FUN this is perfect for you.', 'The hotel features a nice inside courtyard with atrium and there is art work throughout', 'The hotel has nightly activities, like a “mixology” presentation at the bar (which is basically just the bartender describing how to make a drink and giving you about a shot worth of free).', 'The hotel has a Carousel Bar.', 'Plat 99 is a high-end lounge with the midwestern hospitality.', 'The hotel has a decent drink selection, although I was out of mint and couldn’t make a mojito (which was on the drink menu).', 'This hotel features complimentary wireless Internet access.', 'Extended Stay America “Extraordinary”', "The hotel has a dock across the street at their sister property on the I tercoadtal (and I believe they even loan fishing gear. There isn't really room service but they have a delivery set up with Chik Fil A from across the street.", 'The hotel has scavenger hunts, ranger wildlife lessons, and free chocolate.', 'The hotel has a nice pool in the courtyard that we enjoyed very much.', 'This hotel has two pools on site!', 'The hotel has a full house, the innkeeper was so nice and extremely gracious.', '', 'The hotel has a small welcome bag with cookies and water and papers letting you know where all the food delivery locations and numbers.']

preds: ['The hotel is a gem in the heart of Philadelphia. It\'s a cozy, quaint, and charming property. The decor is chic and attractive: big wooden desk, hardwood floors, couches and throw pillows: Looks more like a friend\'s apartment than a hotel. Free breakfast is always a plus for those of us with limited time. It\'s not a hot breakfast (I\'ve had so many mass-produced bad ones, so trust me on that) but greek yogurt, a huge croissant, an orange and some cranberry juice hits the spot! They leave it at your door though, instead of ringing your bell to wake you up. So if you ask for it to be delivered at 7 a.m., check outside your door; by 7:01 it WILL be there. Coffee, a variety of teas, cold and hot water, as well as ice and a bowl of assorted fruit are available 24/7 in the lobby. There are doorbells for each room, and the hotel can only be accessed after hours if you have a key card. Floors are acessible with a keycard as well, for extra protection. The staff is very polite: one of the few places in Philly where someone will actually say "good morning" to you (No, seriously. I lived there for 5 years, so trust me on that). They\'re also extremely helpful. When I checked in the night before, the gentleman at the reservation desk called to make sure I had a cab waiting for me at 8:15 the next morning so that I could make my speaking engagement on time. While I\'ve read a few reviews talking about the noise level of this place. My room was closest to the reception desk and I never heard a peep. There were people out and about, but I didn\'t hear a thing.
